  "prompt": "How much salary in Indian rupees is considered good in japan?",
  "response": "The perception of a \"good\" salary in Japan can vary significantly based on factors such as location, occupation, and lifestyle. However, as a general guideline:\n\n1. **Average Salary**: In Japan, the average annual salary is around \u00a54 million to \u00a55 million (approximately \u20b925 lakhs to \u20b931 lakhs) as of recent data. \n\n2. **Cost of Living**: The cost of living can be high, especially in major cities like Tokyo and Osaka. For instance, a monthly salary of around \u00a5300,000 (approximately \u20b91.85 lakhs) could be considered decent for a comfortable lifestyle in urban areas.\n\n3. **Industry Variations**: Salaries can vary by industry. For example, IT professionals, engineers, and medical professionals may earn higher salaries, often exceeding \u00a56 million annually (approximately \u20b937 lakhs).\n\nIn summary, a salary of around \u00a54 million (\u20b925 lakhs) or more can be viewed as good, particularly if it allows for a comfortable living situation in Japan. Personal circumstances, lifestyle choices, and family size will also influence what is considered a good salary for an individual or family.",
